  Cele told the community members, who attended his briefing at the police station, that other crimes have also spiked area. He said his visit was to ensure the police are doing their jobs to keep the community safe and apprehending criminals who have been terrorising the community recently. After addressing the police, Cele, joined the police convoy that went around Edendale to check-in with residents and assure the community that their safety is the utmost concern. “The community here has grown and with that more and more gangsters and criminals have flocked to the area while the police resources have not grown,” “The last time I visited the (Plessislaer) station I was not impressed however I have noticed an improvement and want this improvement to continue so our area can be certified as safe for our residents,” said Cele.